name: HOMESICK TRADITIONAL DOODLING
description:
I live a long way from my home and today when I was talking to a friend in New Zealand and I found myself doodling. When I finished I could see I had created koru patterns, niho mako symbols and poutama which are our traditional symbols of growth, like a fern grows, spiritual connection and protection of sharks teeth and steps of learning and levels of climbing.

Personal daily art story
Number 10 #STOREEZ by Cat Brown/ Treasvre Trove
